:{{see|Rescue}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
IPA: /ЋИres.kju/
*{{audio|en-us-rescue.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[rescopuen]]'', {{OF.}} ''[[rescourre]], [[rescurre]], [[rescorre]]''; {{L.}} prefix ''[[re-]]'' re- + ''[[excutere]]'' to shake or drive out; ex out + quatere to shake. See [[Qtash]] to crush, [[Rercussion]].

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|rescu|e}}
# To [[free]] or [[deliver]] from any [[confinement]], [[violence]], [[danger]], or [[evil]].
# To [[liberate]] from actual [[restraint]].
# To [[remove]] or [[withdraw]] from a state of exposure to evil.
#:''to '''rescue''' a prisoner from the enemy''
#:''to '''rescue''' seamen from destruction''

====Synonyms====
To [[retake]], [[recapture]], [[free]], [[deliver]], [[liberate]], [[release]], [[save]].

